# Styling and Components Guide

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- Tailwind v3
- Use Tailwind's utility classes for styling
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use custom theme values from [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js)
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale
- Use Tailwind's color palette for consistency

## Component Organization
- UI components go in `/src/components/ui`
- Page-specific components in `/src/components/[feature]`
- Maintain component composition pattern
- Keep components small and focused

## shadcn/ui Components
- shadcn-ui@2.3.0 compatibility Tailwind v3
- Install components using the CLI: `pnpm dlx shadcn-ui@2.3.0 add [component]`
- Customize components in `/src/components/ui`
- Use shadcn/ui's built-in dark mode support
- Follow shadcn/ui's composition patterns
- Available components:
  - Button
  - Card
  - Dialog
  - Form
  - Input
  - Select
  - etc.

## Best Practices
- Use CSS variables for theme values
- Implement proper dark mode support
- Use cn() utility for conditional classes
- Keep consistent component APIs
- Use proper semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper accessibility attributes
